law.text:
The Department shall have a unit for research and development that shall:
compile accurate statistics and reliable information on all aspects of the juvenile program of the State;
monitor current developments in the field of juvenile services;
assess existing programs and activities, including youth services bureaus;
help develop new or improved means, including greater utilization of youth services bureaus under § 9-233 of this subtitle, to prevent juvenile offenses and control and treat juvenile offenders;
if necessary, initiate studies to help the Secretary in general planning and program development for the Department; and
for these and related purposes, use research and information available from all sources.
